{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4e4cd72f-61dd-4f5b-aaee-c298c28af986","content":"Two things change with xUnit v3 + MTP:\n\n### 1. Filter syntax changes\n\nThe VSTest `--filter` syntax (`FullyQualifiedName~X&Category=Y`) is replaced by MTP's `--filter` which uses a different expression language:\n\n```bash\n# Old (VSTest / xUnit v2):\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# New (MTP / xUnit v3):\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nKey differences:\n- **`&`** → **`and`** (logical operators are words: `and`, `or`, `not`)\n- `~` (contains), `=` (equals), `!=` (not equals) still work\n- Parentheses work for grouping: `(A or B) and C`\n\n### 2. `--filter` must go after `--`\n\nWith `UseMicrosoftTestingPlatformRunner=true`, arguments are passed to the MTP runner via `--`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nOr run the test executable directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n### Your CI command\n\n```bash\n# Before\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n\n# After\ndotnet test -- --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests and Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nNo code changes needed — your `[Trait(\"Category\", \"Smoke\")]` attribute works the same in xUnit v3.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fd098fa9-dd84-4324-aaf8-d695cfee79b0","outputTokens":429,"requestId":"D006:180DF7:5F9ECE5:6AE3617:69EC1008"},"id":"4f51adff-e266-43e1-8dbd-dae9d96e248a","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:51:29.826Z","parentId":"5a6e136b-17af-429f-be08-47c39a398c45"}
